===Etymology===
Latin [[bucolicus]], from Greek [[βουκολικός]] (būcolicos) "rustic, pastoral; meter used by pastoral poets", from [[βούκολος]] (būcolos) "cowherd"—[[βοῦς]] (būs) "cow" + [[-κολος]] (-colos) "keeper, tender"; + [[-ικός]] (-icos) "-ic".

